      "text": "jQuery vs JavaScript"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "jQuery was created in 2006 by John Resig. \nIt was designed to handle Browser Incompatibilities and to simplify HTML DOM Manipulation, Event Handling, Animations, and Ajax."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "However, after JavaScript Version 5 (2009), most of the jQuery utilities can be solved with a few lines of standard JavaScript:"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Hiding HTML Elements"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Hide an HTML Element:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "myElement.hide();"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "myElement.style.display = \"none\";"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Showing HTML Elements"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Show an HTML Element:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "myElement.show();"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "myElement.style.display = \"\";"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Styling HTML Elements"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Change the font size of an HTML element:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "$(\"#demo\").css(\"font-size\",\"35px\");"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
